Show HN: Beautiful, fast, web-based bill splitting
text:
Hi HN:

I really think I've perfected bill splitting - afaik this is the first app that let's you split items into fractions (e.g. splitting a pitcher into thirds). You just need to take a photo of the receipt and Torte will handle the math. This makes dining out way less stressful for you and your friends when someone shouldn't or can't split the bill evenly. Please enjoy and pressure test! (USD-only)

I do recommend you download the app-based version for a smoother experience, but your friends do not need to download the app to join the bill and split.

APPLE https://apps.apple.com/us/app/torte-fast-bill-splitting/id14...

ANDROID https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.torte.pay

(Torte was formerly a complete mobile order and mobile payment POS that I beta tested in several restaurants. I've walked it back to bill splitting in order to focus on other projects.)

title: RDMA is Turing complete, we just did not know it yet
GCP requiring sales team approval now for basic quota
text:
I've been using GCP for easily a decade now, since it was just App Engine Python 2.5.

I created a new billing account for a new open source project / company, and lo and behold, to access anything more than basic CPUs and quotas, you need to call sales.

Sales doesn't care about small fish, of course, because they are probably paid on commission; the person on the other end of the phone wanted to know our "company name" and "what we were using the CPUs for" (it's an open source project, we are compiling code, not sure what else to say).

After being a GCP loyalist for as long as I have, I'm sad to see this condition. Has anyone else experienced this? Can anyone else share tips about how best to gain quota / access to resources, when you are willing to pay? Yes, I'm already opening an AWS account, but it will take time to learn the equivalent systems in other clouds.
